anets%20that%20could%20carry%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EComets%20may%20hold%20the%20secret%20to%20finding%20alien%20life%2C%20according%20to%20new%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20at%20Cambridge%20University%20propose%20that%20comets%20may%20%26quot%3Bbounce%26quot%3B%20around%20the%20universe%2C%20carrying%20the%20essential%20ingredients%20to%20create%20life%20on%20alien%20worlds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20their%20theory%20is%20correct%2C%20it%20could%20help%20narrow%20down%20the%20search%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-exoplanets-discovered-astronomers-find-water-alien-worlds-life-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexoplanets%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20have%20the%20correct%20conditions%20for%20a%20comet%20to%20deliver%20the%20building%20blocks%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20possible%20that%20the%20molecules%20that%20led%20to%20life%20on%20Earth%20came%20from%20comets%2C%20so%20the%20same%20could%20be%20true%20for%20planets%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20galaxy%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20first%20author%20Richard%20Anslow%20from%20Cambridge's%20Institute%20of%20Astronomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20it's%20still%20not%20quite%20clear%20how%20life%20starts%20on%20a%20planet%2C%20a%20leading%20theory%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcomets-brought-first-phosphorus-dna-chemical-to-earth-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomets%20carry%20%26quot%3Bprebiotic%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20molecules%20that%20can%20develop%20into%20life%2C%20provided%20they%20land%20safe%20and%20sound%20on%20the%20right%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20deliver%20their%20organic%20molecules%2C%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcomet-heading-earth-bright-outshine-stars-scientists-c-2023-a32023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecomets%3C%2Fa%3E%20need%20to%20travel%20fairly%20slowly%2C%20at%20about%20nine%20miles%20per%20second%2C%20per%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2023%2F11%2F231114215641.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20accompanying%20the%20findings.%20Any%20faster%20and%20the%20molecules%20would%20be%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20modeled%20different%20scenarios%20to%20see%20how%20planetary%20systems%20and%20their%20stars%20would%20pull%20at%20a%20traveling%20comet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20specifically%20looked%20at%20systems%20carrying%20rocky%20planets%20around%20low-mass%20stars%20%E2%80%94%20stars%20that%20are%20smaller%20than%20our%20sun.%20These%20types%20of%20planets%20have%20been%20studied%20as%20prime%20candidates%20to%20carry%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20found%20that%2C%20in%20most%20cases%2C%20a%20comet%20speeding%20through%20a%20planetary%20system%20around%20a%20low-mass%20star%20would%20travel%20too%20quickly%20to%20seed%20life%20on%20a%20planet%20in%20the%20habitable%20zone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20one%20notable%20exception%3A%20if%20the%20planet%20is%20part%20of%20a%20planetary%20system%20called%20%26quot%3Bpeas%20in%20a%20pod%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20the%20planets%20are%20in%20very%20close%20alignment%2C%20this%20string%20of%20planets%20could%20slow%20the%20comet%20down%20as%20it%20is%20captured%20in%20its%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20kicking%20a%20football%20all%20the%20way%20across%20the%20football%20pitch%20in%20one%20massive%20shot%20versus%20dribbling%20it%20slowly%20with%20lots%20of%20different%20kicks%20between%20the%20players%2C%26quot%3B%20Amy%20Bonsor%2C%20an%20astrophysicist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20way%20to%20get%20the%20velocity%20really%20low%20is%20to%20have%20lots%20and%20lots%20of%20planets%2C%20kick%20the%20ball%20between%20them%2C%20and%20bring%20it%20with%20that%20low%20velocity%20down%20to%20the%20habitable%20planet%20to%20deliver%20your%20organics%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bonsor%2C%20who%20is%20an%20author%20on%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Bonsor%20said%20the%20research%20suggests%20a%20low-mass%20planetary%20system%20is%20less%20likely%20to%20carry%20life%20than%20a%20system%20with%20a%20brighter%20star.%20In%20these%20systems%2C%20planets%20can%20be%20farther%20away%20from%20their%20star%2C%20which%20means%20the%20comets%20don't%20have%20to%20pick%20up%20quite%20so%20much%20speed%20to%20reach%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20all%20super%20excited%20in%20the%20community%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20can%20find%20habitable%20zone%20planets%20around%20low-mass%20stars.%20And%20these%20are%20really%20interesting%20planets%20and%20we%20should%20be%20studying%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBonsor%20added%20that%20she's%20not%20alone%20in%20saying%20that%20such%20planets%20may%20be%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20habitable%20than%20an%20Earth-like%20planet%20around%20a%20sun%20similar%20to%20ours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20were%20published%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20Proceedings%20of%20the%20Royal%20Society%20A%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbouncing-comet-could-deliver-life-to-alien-planets-study-finds-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700051833000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6554a8e74ca513d82429a156%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbouncing-comet-could-deliver-life-to-alien-planets-study-finds-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20could%20help%20narrow%20down%20the%20search%20for%20exoplanets%20that%20have%20the%20correct%20conditions%20for%20a%20comet%20to%20deliver%20the%20building%20blocks%20of%20life.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mguenot%40businessinsider.com%20(Marianne%20Guenot)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A52%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbouncing-com