%20more%20than%2090%20per%20cent%20utilisation%20since%202021%2C%20signalling%20its%20need%20for%20additional%20capacity%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcwit-first-phase-likely-to-be-operational-by-dec-2024-karan-adani-123111500714_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcwit-first-phase-likely-to-be-operational-by-dec-2024-karan-adani-123111500714_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcwit-first-phase-likely-to-be-operational-by-dec-2024-karan-adani-123111500714_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI-Powered%20Robot%20Chemist%20Finds%20Molecule%20To%20Make%20Oxygen%20On%20Mars%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20robot%20chemist%20has%20synthesised%20compounds%20that%20could%20be%20used%20to%20generate%20oxygen%20from%20water.%20Powered%20by%20artificial%20intelligence%20(AI)%2C%20the%20robot%20analysed%20meteorites%20from%20Mars%2C%20%3Cem%3Espace.com%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%20in%20a%20report.%20Scientists%20said%20the%20discovery%20will%20help%20future%20crewed%20missions%20to%20Mars%2C%20in%20which%20oxygen%20will%20be%20needed%2C%20not%20just%20for%20astronauts%20to%20breathe%2C%20but%20also%20for%20use%20as%20rocket%20propellant%2C%20the%20outlet%20further%20said%20in%20its%20report.%20Producing%20oxygen%20from%20substances%20found%20on%20the%20Red%20Planet%20will%20do%20away%20with%20the%20need%20to%20carry%20a%20bunch%20of%20oxygen-producing%20materials%20from%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20study%20detailing%20the%20experiment%20has%20been%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Nature%20Synthesis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20came%20to%20scientists%20after%20recent%20discovery%20of%20significant%20reserves%20of%20frozen%20water%20ice%20on%20the%20Martian%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20compounds%20created%20by%20the%20robot%20chemist%2C%20known%20as%20catalysts%2C%20are%20capable%20of%20spurring%20chemical%20reactions%20that%20%26quot%3Bsplit%26quot%3B%20water%20molecules%20to%20generate%20oxygen%20and%20hydrogen%20gas%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fmars-oxygen-ai-robot-chemist-splitting-water%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Espace.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Martian%20meteorites%20on%20which%20experiment%20was%20carried%20out%20were%20rocks%20that%20crashed%20down%20on%20Earth%20after%20cosmic%20impacts%20blasted%20them%20off%20the%20Red%20Planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20scanning%20the%20rocks%20using%20a%20laser%2C%20the%20AI-powered%20robot%20calculated%20more%20than%203.7%20million%20molecules%20it%20could%20make%20from%20six%20different%20metallic%20elements%20in%20the%20rocks%20-%20iron%2C%20nickel%2C%20manganese%2C%20magnesium%2C%20aluminium%20and%20calcium.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20robot%20chemist%20worked%20on%20the%20samples%20for%20six%20weeks%20without%20any%20human%20intervention%20and%20synthesised%20243%20different%20molecules.%20The%20best%20one%20it%20analysed%20could%20split%20water%20at%20minus%2037%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20cold%20temperature%20found%20on%20none%20other%20than%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20a%20boy%2C%20I%20dreamed%20of%20interstellar%20exploration%2C%26quot%3B%20Jun%20Jiang%2C%20co-senior%20author%20of%20the%20study%20and%20a%20scientist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Science%20and%20Technology%20of%20China%20in%20Hefei%20told%20Space.com.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20when%20we%20finally%20saw%20that%20the%20catalysts%20made%20by%20the%20robot%20could%20actually%20produce%20oxygen%20by%20splitting%20water%20molecules%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20my%20dream%20was%20coming%20true.%20I%20even%20started%20to%20imagine%20that%20I%2C%20myself%2C%20will%20live%20on%20Mars%20in%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20scientists%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScientists%20said%20it%20would%20have%20taken%20a%20human%20scientist%202%2C000%20years%20to%20find%20the%20best%20catalyst%20using%20conventional%20methods.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700050740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-12%2Fmars-generic-pixabay-650_650x400_71514600798.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fai-powered-chemist-finds-molecule-to-make-oxygen-on-mars-4576545%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20robot%20chemist%20worked%20on%20the%20samples%20from%20Mars%20for%20six%20weeks%20without%20any%20human%20intervention%20and%20synthesised%20243%20different%20molecules.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fai-powered-chemist-finds-molecule-to-make-oxygen-on-mars-4576545%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fai-powered-chemist-finds-molecule-to-make-oxygen-on-mars-4576545%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fai-powered-chemist-finds-molecule-to-make-oxygen-on-mars-4576545%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Drug%20addict%20murders%20wife%2C%20hangs%20himself%20in%20Bareilly%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700050644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105237645%2Cimgsize-697426.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbareilly%2Fup-drug-addict-murders-wife-hangs-himself-in-bareilly%2Farticleshow%2F105237667.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rameshwar%20alias%20Maiku%20Lal%20(30)%20married%20Seema%20Devi%20(28)%20in%202014%20and%20the%20couple%20has%20two%20children.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ASIF%20ANSARI%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fbareilly%2Fup-drug-addict-murders-wife-hangs-himself-in-bareilly%2Farticleshow%2F105237667.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%