20Global%20Talent%20Competitiveness%20Index%20has%20seen%20India%20fall%20sharply%20down%20from%20rank%2083%20ten%20years%20ago%20to%20rank%20103%20in%20its%20latest%20report%20out%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20total%20of%20134%20countries%20have%20been%20ranked%20and%20presently%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insead.edu%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2F2023-11%2Fgtci-2023-report.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20finds%20itself%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20sandwiched%20between%20Algeria%20(a%20rank%20higher%20at%20102)%20and%20Gautemala%20(at%20rank%20104).%20All%20three%20are%20classified%20as%20lower-%20middle%20income%20countries.%20Among%20other%20countries%20ranking%20better%20than%20India%20are%20Rwanda%2C%20Paraguay%2C%20Tunisia%2C%20Namibia%2C%20Bolivia%2C%20Ghana%2C%20El%20Salvador%2C%20Gambia%2C%20Kenya%2C%20Morocco%20and%20Eswatini.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20is%20well%20below%20the%20median%20score%20of%20the%20countries%20evaluated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDeveloped%20by%20prestigious%20chain%20of%20business%20schools%20INSEAD%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insead.edu%2Fnews%2F2023-global-talent-competitiveness-index-celebrates-a-decade-pioneering-talent-insights%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eindex%20measures%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9Chow%20countries%20and%20cities%20grow%2C%20attract%20and%20retain%20talent.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20It%20says%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Cprovides%20a%20unique%20resource%20for%20decision%20makers%20to%20understand%20the%20global%20talent%20competitiveness%20picture%20and%20develop%20strategies%20to%20boost%20their%20economies.%E2%80%9D%20The%20index%20uses%20two%20sub-indices%20%E2%80%93%20input%20and%20output.%20The%20input%20measures%20regulatory%20and%20business%20environments%2C%20as%20well%20as%20steps%20being%20taken%20to%20foster%20talent%20and%20retain%20it.%20The%20output%20side%20evaluates%20the%20quality%20of%20talent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20steep%20fall%20that%20must%20concern%20India%2C%20with%20the%20government%20often%20citing%20scores%20on%20certain%20business%20indices%2C%20%E2%80%98Ease%20of%20Doing%20Business%E2%80%99%20and%20even%20the%20controversial%20World%20Bank-led%20%E2%80%98Doing%20Business%E2%80%99%20scores%20to%20make%20its%20case.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.worldbank.org%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fstatement%2F2021%2F09%2F16%2Fworld-bank-group-to-discontinue-doing-business-report%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWorld%20Bank%20Report%20on%20%E2%80%98Doing%20Business%E2%80%99%20was%20dropped%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20due%20to%20irregularities%20in%20which%20it%20was%20measured.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20performance%20in%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EGlobal%20Talent%20Competitiveness%20Index%20(GTCI)%20is%20the%20worst%20amongst%20that%20of%20the%20BRICS%20countries.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%20remains%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20BRICS%20group%20of%20countries%20at%20rank%2040%2C%20Russia%20is%20at%2052%2C%20South%20Africa%20at%2068%20and%20Brazil%20is%20ranked%20at%2069.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20(page%2036)%20notes%20that%20India%20%E2%80%9Cremains%20the%20lowest-ranked%20BRICS%20member%20at%20103rd.%20In%20the%20years%20to%202020%2C%20India%20saw%20its%20talent%20competitiveness%20increase%2C%20but%20it%20has%20regressed%20in%20each%20of%20the%20three%20years%20since.%20A%20major%20reason%20for%20this%20fall%20in%20GTCI%20rankings%20is%20a%20slump%20in%20business%20sentiment%2C%20which%20has%20had%20a%20detrimental%20effect%20on%20the%20ability%20to%20%E2%80%98Attract%20talent%E2%80%99%20(now%20ranked%20132nd%20of%20134)%E2%80%94whether%20that%20is%20talent%20from%20overseas%20(127th%20in%20External%20Openness%20sub-pillar)%20or%20from%20within%20the%20country%20(129th%20in%20Internal%20Openness)%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20also%20refers%20to%20%E2%80%9Can%20increased%20skills%20mismatch%2C%20and%20a%20greater%20difficulty%20in%20finding%20skilled%20employees%2C%20pushing%20India%20to%20121st%20in%20both%20the%20%E2%80%98Employability%E2%80%99%20sub-pillar%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98Vocational%20and%20Technical%20Skills%E2%80%99%20pillar.%E2%80%9D%20The%20report%20does%20record%20%E2%80%9CGlobal%20Knowledge%20Skills%2C%20the%20second%20of%20the%20Output-related%20pillars%2C%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20best-performing%20area%2C%20where%20innovation%20and%20software%20development%20are%20driving%20its%2069th%20position%20in%20the%20Talent%20Impact%20sub-pillar.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20report%2C%20other%20emerging%20countries%20have%20shown%20improvements%20on%20this%20index%2C%20with%20China%2C%20Indonesia%20and%20Mexico%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insead.edu%2Fnews%2F2023-global-talent-competitiveness-index-celebrates-a-decade-pioneering-talent-insights%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebeing%20cited%20for%20special%20mention%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20%E2%80%9CSeveral%20of%20the%20largest%20emerging%20economies%20are%20among%20the%20best%20improvers%20over%20the%20past%20decade%3A%20Notable%20examples%20include%3A%20China%20has%20moved%20from%20being%20a%20talent%20mover%20to%20a%20talent%20champion%3B%20Indonesia%20is%20one%20of%20the%20countries%20with%20the%20greatest%20strides%20in%20talent%20competitiveness%20over%20the%20past%20decade%3B%20Mexico%20has%20moved%20from%20being%20a%20talent%20laggard%20to%20a%20talent%20mover%3B%20and%20Brazil%20has%20progressed%20may%20well%20soon%20categorise%20as%20a%20talent%20mover.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESingapore%2C%20Switzerland%20and%20the%20United%20States%20are%20among%20the%20top%20three%20countries%20on%20the%20scale.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEuropean%20countries%20continue%20to%20dominate%20the%20%E2%80%98Top%2025%E2%80%99%20rankings.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20Japan%20has%20dropped%20out%20from%20top%2025%2C%20and%20South%20Korea%20has%20moved%20up%20in%20its%20place.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700046009000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24001805%2FF4NKlFIWcAAT_Qt.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Findia-slides-sharply-on-global-talent-competitiveness-index-worst-among-the-brics-group%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20India%20slid%20from%2083%20to%20103%20in%20the%20rankings%2C%20China%20is%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20group%20at%20rank%2040.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Findia-slides-sharply-on-global-talent-competitiveness-index-worst-among-the-brics-group%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Edinburgh%20Film%20Festival%20Taps%20Picturehouse%20Head%20of%20Acquisitions%20Paul%20Ridd%20as%20New%20Director%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700046000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FPaul-Ridd-Edinburgh-Film-Festival.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235791165%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Edinburgh%20International%20Film%20Festival%20has%20tapped%20Picturehouse%20Entertainment%20head%20of%20acquisitions%20Paul%20Ridd%20as%20its%20new%20director.%20Ridd%20will%20join%20in%20December.%20His%20first%20festival%2C%20the%20event%E2%80%99s%2077th%20anniversary%2C%20will%20take%20place%20in%20August%202024%2C%20with%20specific%20dates%20to%20be%20announced.%20The%20festival%20returned%20for%20its%2076th%20edition%C2%A0earlier%20this%20year%20following%20financial%20difficulties.%20It%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Naman